.TH LOA-OBSIDIAN-DOCTOR 1 "2026-03-23" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
obsidian doctor \- Validate Obsidian vault setup for Alexandria sync
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> obsidian doctor
.br
alexandria> obsidian doctor /path/to/your/vault
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs environment checks for an Obsidian vault:
.br
\fB- vault path\fR (exists and is a directory)
.br
\fB- write access\fR (probe file write/delete)
.br
\fB- required folders\fR (Alexandria managed folders including Bases/Templates)
.br
\fB- required GUI files\fR (GUI Home, Saved Searches, Bookmarks, Genres MOC,
base files, templates/bookmarks config)
.br
Use this before first sync or when sync/open behavior looks wrong.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> obsidian doctor
.TP
alexandria> obsidian doctor ~/Documents/MyVault
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1), loa-export-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian-sync(1), loa-obsidian-open(1)
.SH AUTHOR
